---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn about our robotics club, our mission, and our team of student engineers."
>
  <div class="py-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          About Our Voorheesville Robotics Club
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Inspiring the next generation of engineers and innovators
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          We're a student-led high school robotics club dedicated to learning through hands-on
          engineering challenges. Our mission is to inspire students to pursue careers in STEM
          fields by providing practical experience in robotics, programming, and teamwork.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <p>Throughout the year, our club members:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Design and build robots for competitions like FIRST Robotics and VEX</li>
          <li>Learn programming languages including Python, C++, and Arduino</li>
          <li>Use CAD software to design mechanical components</li>
          <li>Work with electronics, sensors, and motor controllers</li>
          <li>Collaborate on team projects and share knowledge</li>
          <li>Participate in regional and national competitions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Meeting Schedule</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Regular Meetings:</strong> Wednesdays, 3:30-5:30 PM in Room 204<br>
          <strong>Build Sessions:</strong> Saturdays, 10:00 AM-2:00 PM in the Makerspace<br>
          <strong>Competition Season:</strong> Additional hours as needed
        </p>

        <h2>Club History</h2>
        <p>
          Founded in 2018, our club has grown from 5 founding members to over 30 active participants.
          We've competed in numerous regional competitions and made it to nationals twice. Our club
          has won several awards for robot design, programming, and team spirit.
        </p>

        <h2>Achievements</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>2024 Regional Champions - FIRST Robotics Competition</li>
          <li>2023 Excellence Award - VEX Robotics</li>
          <li>2022 Innovation Award - State Competition</li>
          <li>Published 50+ blog posts and tutorials</li>
          <li>Built 20+ robots for competition and learning</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>
          Interested in joining? No experience necessary! We welcome students of all skill levels.
          Come to any Wednesday meeting to learn more or <a href="/contact">contact us</a> for more information.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Contact us:</strong> robotics@school.edu<br>
          <strong>Follow us:</strong> <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> |
          <a href="https://youtube.com">YouTube</a> |
          <a href="https://discord.com">Discord</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
